==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fragrancy
<hw>Fra"gran*cy</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr> }</mhw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>fragrantia</ets>: cf.
OF. <ets>fragrance</ets>.]</ety> <def>The quality of being fragrant;
sweetness of smell; a sweet smell; a pleasing odor; perfume.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Eve separate he spies,⟦br⟧
Veiled in a cloud of <qex>fragrance</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The goblet crowned,⟦br⟧
Breathed aromatic <qex>fragrancies</qex> around.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fragrant</ent>⟦br⟧
